      %br
      %h4 What is Hack Club?
      %p
        We help high schoolers start after-school coding clubs. We'll
        provide absolutely everything needed to start and run a club
        from scratch—curriculum, community, leadership training, and
        events... a club-in-a-box. Our primary goal is to make it easy
        for club leaders to focus on cultivating a fantastic club
        community—we'll handle the rest.
      %h4 What does a Hack Club look like?
      %p
        Each Hack Club meets weekly for an hour and a half. The
        structure varies club to club, but most meetings involve
        members building projects and  sharing them with one another.
        Club leaders use our curriculum to teach new members to code
        while they're working on projects.
      %h4 What is Hacking?
      %p
        When we say "hack", we're referring to the "life hack" type of
        hacking. Simply put, hacking is creative problem solving—and it
        often includes code. Hack Club teaches students to code and to
        use coding skills to solve problems, not to crack into your
        bank account.
      %h4 Have any other questions?
      %p
        = link_to 'Please send us an email', 'mailto:team@hackclub.com'
        or
        = link_to 'chat with us on the Hack Club Slack!',
          'https://slack.hackclub.com/'
